      "shortest": true,
      "solution": "s = input().strip()\n\nmirror = {'0':'0','1':'1','2':'5','5':'2','6':'9','8':'8','9':'6'}\n\ntry:\n    print(\"\".join(mirror[c] for c in reversed(s)))\nexcept:\n    print(\"INVALID\")",
      "statement": "Given a number as a string of digits, create it's mirror version.\n\nThe mirror is obtained by:\n1. Reversing the digits .\n2. Replacing each digit with it's mirror equivalent.\n\nMirror map:\n| Digit | Mirror |\n| ----- | ------ |\n| 0     | 0      |\n| 1     | 1      |\n| 2     | 5      |\n| 5     | 2      |\n| 6     | 9      |\n| 8     | 8      |\n| 9     | 6      |\nDigits <<3, 4, 7 cannot be mirrored>>.\n\nIf the number contains an invalid digit, output <<INVALID>>.",
